ind":"text","text":"said to a woman means, (K, TA,) accord. to the explanation of IAmb, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA sit~a jihaAtiY","text_ar":"يَا سِتَّ جِهَاتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O thou who occupiest the six places in relation to me;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who art above me, below me, before me, behind me, on my right, and on my left"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) as though alluding to her holding the speaker in her possession: (TA:) or it is an incorrect expression; (K;) or it is vulgar, and held in low estimation; (IAar, TA;) and is correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idatiY","text_ar":"سَيِّدَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my lady,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my mistress"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) it may be regarded as a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idatiY","text_ar":"سَيِّدَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Esh-Shiháb El-Kásimee: (TA:) and Es-seyyid 'Eesà Es-Safawee says that it should not be restricted to the class of expression used as vocatives. (MF, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}